did.head: Collection Summary

repository.corpname: Woodson Research Center, Rice University, Houston, Texas

did.abstract: This record group includes correspondence and event planning documents from the Student Center Board, as well as the daily business, publicity, meeting minutes, and memorabilia of the Rice Program Council (RPC).

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Student Association (SA) created the Rice Program Council (RPC) in 1971. It replaced the SA's Student Center Board, the Forum, and the Social Committee to become the official programming arm of the SA. Since its inception, RPC has managed Beer Bike, Esperanza, Rondelet, and other events. As of 2014, they plan all of the above plus Screw Your Roommate, Crush Party, various Willy Week events, and the Welcome Back Concert.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This record group charts the history of the Student Center Board and the Rice Program Council. There are minutes, calendars, contracts, and event glassware.

Boxes 1-7 stored off-site at the Library Service Center. Please request this material via woodson@rice.edu or call 713-348-2586. Box 8 stored onsite at the Woodson Research Center.
